must rule the wiretap

23:12.550 --> 23:14.609
is admissible.
(gavelbangs)

23:14.660 --> 23:17.015
So now what?

23:17.060 --> 23:18.755
We lost the battle.

23:18.790 --> 23:20.792
We haven't lost the war.

23:28.470 --> 23:29.960
Mom, you cheated.

23:30.000 --> 23:32.139
You can't say
you didn't cheat when you did.

23:32.170 --> 23:34.138
I didn't cheat.

23:34.180 --> 23:36.068
You know me.

23:36.110 --> 23:38.169
I talked, I flirted.

23:38.210 --> 23:41.748
Malcolm knows I flirt.

23:41.780 --> 23:43.748
His son never liked me.

23:43.790 --> 23:45.587
That is why
he filled his head

23:45.620 --> 23:47.656
with all this... Why
is the TV over there?

23:47.690 --> 23:49.055
Shouldn't it be
in that corner?

23:49.090 --> 23:50.216
I like it over there.

23:50.260 --> 23:52.228
Hmm.

23:52.260 --> 23:54.854
Is this about me being away?

23:54.900 --> 23:56.822
Is what about you being away?

23:56.860 --> 23:58.168
Well, this parental talking-to.

23:59.070 --> 24:01.038
You were away
for two years, Mom.

24:01.070 --> 24:02.765
Malcolm wanted to.

24:02.800 --> 24:04.609
He had the soul of a vagabond.

24:06.640 --> 24:09.234
I called.

24:09.280 --> 24:11.703
I know.

24:13.750 --> 24:15.945
I'm sorry.

24:21.260 --> 24:23.216
I love you.

24:23.260 --> 24:25.455
You know that,
don't you?

24:32.900 --> 24:35.095
You know, you really should read

24:35.140 --> 24:36.630
this vagina book.

24:36.670 --> 24:38.262
She talks about the
profound connection

24:38.310 --> 24:39.959
between the brain
and the vagina.

24:40.010 --> 24:41.705
It really explains a lot.

24:41.740 --> 24:43.640
Sounds great, Mom.

24:43.680 --> 24:46.547
You know, you've gotten
a lot more ironical lately.

24:46.580 --> 24:48.548
Did you know that?

24:48.580 --> 24:50.138
Is it about Will?

24:50.180 --> 24:52.512
What?
Will?

24:52.550 --> 24:54.552
Your boss. Will?

24:54.590 --> 24:56.615
Is that what
this is about?

24:57.660 --> 24:59.821
Oh, my God.

24:59.860 --> 25:01.259
(sighs, sniffles)

25:01.300 --> 25:04.599
Don't get in a fight.

25:04.630 --> 25:06.268
I had to tell her something.

25:06.300 --> 25:08.996
She thought Will was gay,
and he was into me.

25:09.040 --> 25:11.031
So you told her
I slept with him?

25:11.070 --> 25:12.662
No. No, I would
never tell her that.

25:12.710 --> 25:14.735
I told her you had
a crush on him.

25:14.780 --> 25:15.906
Oh!

25:15.940 --> 25:17.544
She thought we were gay!

25:17.580 --> 25:19.309
So, you just say,
"It's none of your business."

25:19.350 --> 25:21.568
Have you ever tried that
with Mom?

25:21.620 --> 25:24.088
It's not his fault, Alicia.

25:24.120 --> 25:25.587
We're family.

25:25.620 --> 25:27.679
We don't hide things
from each other.

25:34.660 --> 25:35.752
DALE:
Well, that's the thing.

25:35.800 --> 25:38.564
I-I don't know
if I didn't do anything wrong.

25:38.600 --> 25:40.090
Okay.

25:40.130 --> 25:42.690
And that was your boyfriend,
Mr. Lamborne, admitting

25:42.740 --> 25:43.934
that he committed fraud?

25:43.970 --> 25:45.631
Objection,
Your Honor.
Sustained.

25:45.670 --> 25:48.537
Nothing further, Your Honor.
Tender the witness.

25:50.340 --> 25:51.876
JUDGE:
Mr. Breslow,
any questions?

25:51.910 --> 25:53.047
Uh, nothing, Your Honor.

25:53.080 --> 25:54.775
Uh, Excuse me, Your Honor.

25:54.820 --> 25:56.708
Could you, uh, give us a minute?

25:56.750 --> 25:57.910
Certainly.

25:57.950 --> 25:59.247
(whispering):
You can't let that stand.

25:59.290 --> 26:01.349
The tap makes it sound like
Dale admitted guilt.

26:01.390 --> 26:03.017
No. The judge is
smart enough to see

26:03.060 --> 26:03.958
he was just being a
conscientious CFO.

26:03.990 --> 26:05.252
Dale, let us cross-examine.

26:05.290 --> 26:07.929
The judge has
to have this underlined.
o.

26:07.960 --> 26:08.858
We underline
at the closing.

26:08.900 --> 26:10.891
Dale, you brought me
on for my experience.

26:10.930 --> 26:13.899
My experience
tells me we wait.

26:15.770 --> 26:18.204
Sorry, Diane, Alicia.

26:19.910 --> 26:21.901
You want him to lose.

26:21.940 --> 26:24.272
I want him to lose?

26:24.310 --> 26:25.846
What are we talking about here?

26:25.880 --> 26:27.245
You want Dale to lose.

26:27.280 --> 26:29.009
You want to take
this DOMA issue

26:29.050 --> 26:31.211
to the Supreme Court,
and you can't do it if he wins.

26:31.250 --> 26:32.387
You can't appeal a win!

26:32.420 --> 26:33.853
This is my right hand.

26:33.890 --> 26:35.858
Oh, don't give me that crap!

26:35.890 --> 26:37.881
I'm here to win.

26:39.660 --> 26:41.628
How many times have you argued

26:41.660 --> 26:43.093
before the
Supreme Court?

26:43.130 --> 26:46.190
How many times have you gone
toe-to-toe with Justice Scalia?

26:48.140 --> 26:50.904
_ _ I don't need
to justify my defense to you.

26:52.970 --> 26:55.029
I am here to win.

26:55.080 --> 26:57.901
I am here to win it all!

26:57.950 --> 27:01.169
Everything.

27:01.220 --> 27:03.745
For all of us.

27:05.890 --> 27:08.916
(door opens and closes,
crowd chatter)

27:10.790 --> 27:12.849
He has answered all
of your questions

27:12.890 --> 27:14.027
completely and honestly.

27:14.060 --> 27:15.288
BUCKY:
So you're saying

27:15.330 --> 27:16.854
it was Mr. Lamborne's idea

27:16.900 --> 27:18.765
to commit this fraud?

27:18.800 --> 27:21.860
Yes. A CEO has to
rely on his CFO,

27:21.900 --> 27:24.039
and I guess Ijust
couldn't rely on Dale.

27:24.070 --> 27:26.129
I'm sorry that makes
you angry, Dale,

27:26.170 --> 27:27.307
but you know it's true.

27:27.340 --> 27:29.331
Thank you. Nothing further.

27:31.050 --> 27:32.677
JUDGE FRIEND
Mr. Breslow, anything?

27:32.710 --> 27:33.779
No, Your Honor.

27:33.820 --> 27:35.913
We'll save our rebuttal
for the closmg arguments.

27:35.950 --> 27:38.089
I have a few questions,
Your Honor.
Ma'am, no.

27:39.120 --> 27:41.179
I have a few questions.

27:41.220 --> 27:44.018
I'm leading the defense,
and I say, no questions.

27:44.060 --> 27:44.981
He just lied about you, Dale.

27:45.030 --> 27:47.692
He was your friend,
and he lied to your face.

27:47.730 --> 27:48.856
BRESLOW:
That's why we wait

27:48.900 --> 27:50.026
for the summation.

27:50.060 --> 27:51.721
No. You answer a lie now,
or it sticks.

27:51.770 --> 27:53.021
Ladies and gentlemen
of the defense?

27:53.070 --> 27:54.389
Just a second, Your Honor.

27:54.440 --> 27:55.998
Dale, we don't want our defense
to seem unorganized.

27:56.040 --> 27:57.166
He wants you to lose.

27:57.200 --> 27:59.031
To him, it's not about you.

27:59.070 --> 28:00.162
It's about the issue.

28:00.210 --> 28:02.804
Where do we stand
over there?

28:05.980 --> 28:07.277
It's a mistake.

28:07.310 --> 28:10.347
Mr. Foster, you testified

28:10.380 --> 28:12.985
that the fraud started
with Dale, not you.

28:13.020 --> 28:15.181
Yes. I trusted him.

28:15.220 --> 28:17.188
Mm-hmm. _
Let me play you this tap.

28:17.220 --> 28:19.324
MRS. FOSTER:
Well, that's not your fault,
Vance.

28:19.360 --> 28:21.021
VANCE:
It is my fault...

28:21.060 --> 28:22.049
if it's discovered.

28:22.100 --> 28:24.022
Excuse me. Objection.

28:24.070 --> 28:26.823
The court has already excluded
this tap due

28:26.870 --> 28:28.360
to spousal
shield laws.

28:28.400 --> 28:29.958
JUDGE:
Yes, Mrs. Florrick,
I thought my ruling was clear.

28:30.000 --> 28:32.104
It certainly was clear,
Your Honor.

28:32.140 --> 28:34.028
When Mr. Foster was a defendant,
the tap could not be played.

28:34.080 --> 28:36.002
But he's no longer
a defendant.

28:36.040 --> 28:38.508
He's a witness, and I am using
this tap for impeachment.

28:38.550 --> 28:41.212
There is no spousal privilege
with impeachment.

28:41.250 --> 28:45.038
That seems to be
eminently clear, Buclq.

28:45.090 --> 28:47.308
Doesn't it?

28:47.350 --> 28:51.059
We would preserve our objection
for the record, Your Honor.

28:51.090 --> 28:53.320
JUDGE:
Please continue,
Mrs. Florrick.

28:53.360 --> 28:57.524
VANCE:
If it's discovered,
the extent of this fraud,

28:57.560 --> 29:01.291
I could find myself
facing a grand jury.

29:06.410 --> 29:08.332
I have been authorized
to offer you four months.

29:08.380 --> 29:09.506
Admission of complicity.

29:09.540 --> 29:14.045
$500,000 in
restitution.

29:14.080 --> 29:16.378
I think you would all
agree that this is

29:16.420 --> 29:19.480
a difficult plea bargain for the
Department of Justice to make.

29:19.520 --> 29:21.556
You have ten hours
to give us a yes

29:21.590 --> 29:23.012
or no.
Thank you, sir.

29:23.060 --> 29:24.527
We'll give it
its due consideration.

29:28.600 --> 29:30.488
(door opening)

29:30.530 --> 29:32.760
Wait till he
turns the corner.

29:34.970 --> 29:36.938
Now.

29:36.970 --> 29:38.528
Congratulations, Dale.

29:38.570 --> 29:41.277
I thought he was going to say,
"Four years."

29:41.310 --> 29:42.402
(laughing)

29:42.440 --> 29:45.204
(elevator bell dings)

29:47.920 --> 29:51.242
Thank you, Mr. Nemec.

29:51.290 --> 29:53.542
I... Do I know you?

29:53.590 --> 29:56.115
No. I, uh, saw you in court.

29:56.160 --> 29:57.821
What you and your husband
are doing--

29:57.860 --> 30:00.351
as a gay man-- I thank you.

30:00.390 --> 30:02.392
You're welcome.

30:03.430 --> 30:05.398
MAN:
Mr. Nemec?

30:05.430 --> 30:07.421
(Dale laughing)

30:07.470 --> 30:08.437
DIANE:
That's fantastic.

30:08.470 --> 30:10.392
DALE:
I still can't believe
this is happening.

30:10.440 --> 30:12.101
I mean, look at me.
I'm still shaking.

30:12.140 --> 30:13.835
Come on, Mr.
Breslow. We won.

30:13.880 --> 30:15.871
No, ma'am, we didn't.

30:15.910 --> 30:17.332
I wouldn't take it, Dale.

30:17.380 --> 30:18.608
You're innocent.

30:18.650 --> 30:20.845
But they're coming after me
for 12 years.

30:20.880 --> 30:21.949
And they have the evidence.

30:21.980 --> 30:24.847
Mr. Breslow,
you have an agenda here.

30:24.890 --> 30:26.482
You have a reason
to reject this.

30:26.520 --> 30:28.351
Tell him.
Gladly.

30:28.390 --> 30:29.379
(door opening)
Uh, come on in.

30:31.490 --> 30:34.527
Your husband has been offered
a four-month sentence

30:34.560 --> 30:36.096
and a half-million-dollar fine.

30:36.130 --> 30:37.859
I can't promise better.

30:37.900 --> 30:40.869
In fact, my guess is,
if Dale doesn't take this plea,

30:40.900 --> 30:43.494
he'll be found guilty.

30:43.540 --> 30:45.508
I take no solace in that.

30:45.540 --> 30:48.179
I just think
you've been treated unjustly.

30:48.210 --> 30:50.371
And you have been treated
unjustly for one reason:

30:50.410 --> 30:51.502
you are gay men.

30:51.550 --> 30:54.917
Now, with clever maneuvers,
we can limit your sentence.

30:54.950 --> 30:56.645
Alicia and Diane--
they're clever.

30:56.680 --> 30:58.181
They can manipulate the law,

30:58.220 --> 30:59.517
and they will succeed,
because they're good.

30:59.550 --> 31:02.314
But the law would not change,

31:02.360 --> 31:06.023
and same-sex couples
would still struggle under DOMA.

31:08.000 --> 31:09.524
You're asking us to lose?

31:09.560 --> 31:12.529
Yes. I'm asking you to force
the court to face its hypocrisy.

31:12.570 --> 31:14.891
We want to take this
to the Supreme Court.

31:14.940 --> 31:17.397
You are two picturesque

31:17.440 --> 31:20.307
upper-middle-class gay men
who can't be dismissed easily.

31:20.340 --> 31:22.501
You are exactly
what we need

31:22.540 --> 31:25.600
to pull Justice
Kennedy to our side.

31:25.650 --> 31:27.072
It's not just
about you anymore.

31:27.110 --> 31:28.646
It's about the entire
gay community.

31:28.680 --> 31:32.446
It's about you two sacrificing
so that we can overturn DOMA.

31:39.130 --> 31:41.121
What do you think?

31:42.360 --> 31:44.590
I don't think
you're gonna like what I think.

31:47.130 --> 31:48.495
I can't believe it.

31:48.540 --> 31:50.269
He's a good salesman.

31:50.300 --> 31:51.403
Okay, it's not over yet.

31:51.440 --> 31:54.375
If they're not taking the plea,
we have one option left.

31:54.410 --> 31:55.638
Winning?

31:58.150 --> 32:00.505
ALICIA:
Owen. Hi.

32:00.550 --> 32:01.972
What are you
doing here?

32:02.020 --> 32:03.214
I've been subpoenaed.

32:03.250 --> 32:04.342
You...

32:07.050 --> 32:08.711
I'll be outside.

32:08.760 --> 32:09.954
Thanks, Cary.

32:10.990 --> 32:12.287
(door closes)

32:12.330 --> 32:14.651
It's Malcolm's son--
they want to question me.

32:14.700 --> 32:17.089
You talked to him
about Mom cheating?

32:17.130 --> 32:18.563
He brought up
Henry the oilman.

32:18.600 --> 32:20.261
I-I said I'd
never met him.

32:20.300 --> 32:21.961
They're gonna ask you
what Mom told you,

32:22.000 --> 32:23.399
and she told you
she was cheating with Henry?

32:23.440 --> 32:26.000
What-what do I do?
I mean, if I tell
the truth...

32:26.040 --> 32:27.667
Then Mom's
perjured herself.
Yes.

32:27.710 --> 32:30.201
And she loses the
inheritance, she
loses everything.

32:30.240 --> 32:32.299
But if you lie,
you're perjuring yourself.

32:32.350 --> 32:34.739
What is that?
That's a Class 3 Felony.

32:34.780 --> 32:36.668
Two to five years.
You're-you're kidding me.

32:36.720 --> 32:37.641
(knocking)

32:37.680 --> 32:39.113
Damn it.

32:39.150 --> 32:40.742
I have to get
to court.

32:40.790 --> 32:42.678
Well, um...

32:42.720 --> 32:44.449
okay, what-what
would you do?

32:44.490 --> 32:47.186
What would I do?
The same thing as you.

32:47.230 --> 32:48.720
You tell the truth.

32:51.670 --> 32:53.661
So you're saying,
Mr. Collegio,

32:53.700 --> 32:55.429
that it is
a fact that

32:55.470 --> 32:56.664
Mr._Lamborne
is innocent?

32:56.700 --> 32:58.463
Yes.
And how do you know this?

32:58.510 --> 32:59.568
I'm the head I.T. guy
at TaxLaunch.

32:59.610 --> 33:02.579
I mean, the, uh,
Chief Departmental
Software Officer,

33:02.610 --> 33:04.703
and I know that the
server went down

33:04.750 --> 33:06.001
during the time
in question.

33:06.050 --> 33:08.712
Mr. Lamborne couldn't
have seen or impacted
the fraudulent

33:08.750 --> 33:10.547
returns in question.
Thank you, sir.

33:10.580 --> 33:12.548
No further questions,
Your Honor.

33:12.590 --> 33:14.353
Just one from me, Your Honor.

33:15.560 --> 33:17.687
Mr. Collegio,
in your opinion,

33:17.720 --> 33:20.188
is our client, Dale
Lamborne, an honest man?

33:20.230 --> 33:21.527
Oh, yes, definitely.

33:21.560 --> 33:22.754
I've known him
for ten years.

33:22.800 --> 33:24.392
I'd trust him
with my life.

33:24.430 --> 33:27.319
Thank you.
Uh, just a few questions,
Mr. Collegio.

33:27.370 --> 33:29.167
So, Mr. Collegio,

33:29.200 --> 33:31.407
you know the client,
Mr. Lamborne, personally?

33:31.440 --> 33:33.761
I do.
Have you ever had
a personal sexual

33:33.810 --> 33:36.176
relationship with him?
Objection, Your Honor.
Beyond the scope.

33:36.210 --> 33:38.701
Your Honor, the defense,
in its questioning
of Mr. Collegio

33:38.750 --> 33:41.719
about Mr. Lamborne's
honesty, used him as
a character witness.

33:41.750 --> 33:43.809
They opened the
door to my questions
about personal bias.

33:43.850 --> 33:46.683
(whispers):
You are really
screwing us.

33:46.720 --> 33:49.587
Just playing
long ball, ma'am.

33:52.790 --> 33:54.758
Did you hear me?

33:54.800 --> 33:56.529
Did I... What?

33:56.560 --> 33:59.222
The tap-- it had
an overhear.

33:59.270 --> 34:01.238
What's an overhear?

34:01.270 --> 34:04.159
When the CEO hung up
after Vance hung up,

34:04.210 --> 34:06.269
there were two clicks
on the Wiretap.

34:06.310 --> 34:07.629
There were two
tap disconnects.

34:07.670 --> 34:09.831
It's not just the feds--
there was somebody else

34:09.880 --> 34:10.608
tapping in.
You're talking

34:10.640 --> 34:12.403
about the two
Wiretaps?
Yeah.

34:12.450 --> 34:13.644
It's not just the feds.

34:13.680 --> 34:15.318
Somebody else
was investigating the CEO.

34:15.350 --> 34:17.818
_Who else would be
investigating Vance?

34:17.850 --> 34:19.715
My guess is State.

34:19.750 --> 34:21.047
You need to subpoena
What they have.

34:21.090 --> 34:25.151
They have to give it to you;
you have an ongoing trial.
Yeah.

34:25.190 --> 34:27.420
Thank you.

34:27.460 --> 34:29.496
(Will chuckles)

34:29.530 --> 34:31.225
I_ wouldn't
he to you.

34:31.270 --> 34:34.489
VERONICA: You really
haven't read it?
