agree, Buclq.

35:57.220 --> 35:58.289
Drop these charges,

35:58.320 --> 35:59.844
or we will present
them in court.

35:59.890 --> 36:02.814
You'll lose, and expose
some embarrassing

36:02.860 --> 36:04.589
interagency confusion.

36:06.230 --> 36:08.721
Like I said,
I'll get back to you.

36:15.240 --> 36:16.867
Congratulations.

36:16.900 --> 36:18.731
Thank you.
You just stuck us

36:18.770 --> 36:21.238
with DOMA for another decade.

36:28.880 --> 36:31.849
(thunder rumbling)

36:31.890 --> 36:36.918
VERONICA: Not a bad oven
for such a small kitchen.

36:36.960 --> 36:38.928
You still grumpy?
Nope.

36:38.960 --> 36:40.450
Well, the turkey's
almost done.

36:40.490 --> 36:44.426
Okay, so, I got
three Whites and two reds.

36:44.470 --> 36:46.722
You think that'll
be enough?

36:46.770 --> 36:48.397
Apparently not.

36:48.440 --> 36:49.566
Have you been talking here?

36:49.600 --> 36:51.534
Mom won her probate fight.

36:51.570 --> 36:53.231
Congratulations.
Your sister thinks

36:53.270 --> 36:54.373
(doorbell rings)
we're liars.

36:54.410 --> 36:55.434
Grace, can you get that?

36:55.480 --> 36:57.698
VERONICA: After the years
I put in with Malcolm,

36:57.740 --> 36:59.401
I deserve that money.
I'm fine.

36:59.450 --> 37:01.441
I didn't say anything.
You don't have
to say anything

37:01.480 --> 37:02.640
with that look
of yours.

37:02.680 --> 37:04.580
GRACE:
Mom! It's Grandma!

37:04.620 --> 37:06.019
The other one!

37:06.050 --> 37:07.984
Oh, dear God.
I didn't know
she was coming.

37:08.020 --> 37:10.511
She's coming.

37:10.560 --> 37:11.549
And Peter, too?

37:11.590 --> 37:14.593
Yep. (sighs)

37:16.460 --> 37:18.496
What is this called again,
Cristian?

37:18.530 --> 37:19.622
Saoco.
(Whispers):
Socko.

37:19.670 --> 37:21.638
Pow._
Saoco is
a Cuban drink.

37:21.670 --> 37:22.989
It just needs ice.

37:23.040 --> 37:24.359
It's perfect
for this weather.

37:25.440 --> 37:26.805
I love these Cuban names.

37:26.840 --> 37:29.035
They're so
tropical.
Happy Thanksgiving.

37:29.080 --> 37:30.877
Welcome.
Have you met
Cristian?

37:30.910 --> 37:33.378
You have a lovely home.
Why, thank you.

37:33.410 --> 37:35.446
Ooh. Let me get some glasses

37:35.480 --> 37:36.515
for this...
Socko.

37:36.550 --> 37:37.517
...socko.

37:37.550 --> 37:39.745
ZACH: Hey, Mom, they're
talking about your case.

37:39.790 --> 37:41.451
I'll be right there.

37:41.490 --> 37:42.912
Mom's in the kitchen.

37:42.960 --> 37:45.428
I'm sure she'd love
to talk to you, Jackie.

37:45.460 --> 37:46.984
(thunder rumbling in distance)

37:48.030 --> 37:49.520
(quietly): Okay.

37:49.560 --> 37:50.822
Only one pill.

37:50.860 --> 37:53.522
And no alcohol.

37:53.570 --> 37:54.867
(quietly):
I cross my...

37:54.900 --> 37:57.437
MAN (on TV):
So, I looked at this case,

37:57.470 --> 37:59.665
and when I saw it,
all I saw was that you were

37:59.710 --> 38:01.735
taking this to
the Supreme Court.
(laughs)

38:01.780 --> 38:04.601
Not every case is built
for the Supreme Court.

38:04.650 --> 38:06.675
Sometimes you
just have to Win it.

38:06.710 --> 38:08.769
And that's What I decided here.

38:08.820 --> 38:11.072
We discussed the possibility

38:11.120 --> 38:14.510
of a... of a test case,
but in the final analysis

38:14.560 --> 38:16.653
Mr. Lamborne's freedom was key.

38:16.690 --> 38:18.681
(chuckling)

38:19.890 --> 38:21.551
(doorbell rings)

38:22.960 --> 38:25.394
Hi.

38:25.430 --> 38:27.625
Hey. Having fun?

38:27.670 --> 38:29.092
Got anything stronger?

38:29.140 --> 38:31.768
Yeah, if we raid
the evidence locker.

38:31.810 --> 38:34.529
Don't tempt me.
Hm.

38:34.580 --> 38:36.673
Oh, Whoa, Whoa, no.

38:36.710 --> 38:38.439
(sighs): Yep.

38:38.480 --> 38:40.641
Oh, Cristian,
brought that.

38:40.680 --> 38:42.511
Oh. What is Saoco?

38:42.550 --> 38:43.812
Ay...

38:43.850 --> 38:46.717
JACKIE:
I'm so glad
you decided to visit.

38:46.750 --> 38:50.618
Zach and Grace were
wondering about their
other grandmother.

38:50.660 --> 38:53.026
I heard you nearly
died, Jackie.

38:53.060 --> 38:56.996
A stroke from helping out
with the kids,

38:57.030 --> 38:59.066
by myself.
Well, at least

38:59.100 --> 39:01.432
you got a young companion
out of it.

39:01.470 --> 39:03.438
How much does
he charge?

39:03.470 --> 39:05.529
$40 an hour.

39:05.570 --> 39:07.367
You should consider it.

39:07.410 --> 39:09.776
You won't have to go begging
for male attention.

39:09.810 --> 39:10.970
Yes.

39:11.010 --> 39:14.002
Paying for it seems
to run in your family.

39:14.050 --> 39:15.711
Hi, Mom.

39:16.750 --> 39:18.479
Hi, Veronica.

39:18.520 --> 39:20.909
Hi, darling.

39:20.950 --> 39:24.113
How are you two doing?

39:24.160 --> 39:26.128
So, how's she doing?

39:26.160 --> 39:27.821
Much better.
Good.

39:27.860 --> 39:30.158
She seems happy.
Yes.

39:30.200 --> 39:31.690
Very happy.

39:31.730 --> 39:33.527
She's a funny lady.

39:33.570 --> 39:35.936
What do you mean by that?
(laughs)

39:35.970 --> 39:38.666
She's funny;
she makes me laugh.

39:38.710 --> 39:40.701
Ah. Well, you've
been spending

39:40.740 --> 39:42.469
a lot of time
with her, huh?

39:42.510 --> 39:45.604
Yeah. She has
extended my hours.

39:45.650 --> 39:46.969
Really?

39:47.010 --> 39:49.114
What... Is that necessary?

39:50.520 --> 39:52.647
No.

39:52.690 --> 39:54.612
(chuckles softly)

39:54.660 --> 39:57.549
* Be sure it's true,
when you say I love you... *

39:57.590 --> 39:59.421
Uh, no, thanks.

39:59.460 --> 40:01.519
* A double sin to tell a lie

40:01.560 --> 40:02.629
* What'd I say!

40:02.660 --> 40:03.957
(thunder rumbling)

40:04.000 --> 40:05.968
(Baroque music playing)

40:06.000 --> 40:08.491
So... he's over
here a lot?

40:08.540 --> 40:10.496
Peter? Sometimes.

40:10.540 --> 40:12.167
And you go over
to his place?

40:14.880 --> 40:18.748
Is this because of me?

40:18.780 --> 40:20.748
Of course, Mother.

40:20.780 --> 40:22.748
Everything is
because of you.

40:22.780 --> 40:25.089
You know What I mean.
You can't let go.

40:25.120 --> 40:26.246
Even as a little kid,

40:26.290 --> 40:29.214
you never could let go of
friends or old schoolbooks.

40:29.260 --> 40:32.718
Even your dad--
you never wanted to
let go of his hand.

40:32.760 --> 40:37.049
And now, there's this
person at work-- Will--

40:37.100 --> 40:39.728
and you want him but you
won't let yourself have him,

40:39.770 --> 40:41.226
because then
you'll be like me.

40:41.270 --> 40:43.761
(thunder rumbling in distance)
(exhales)

40:45.710 --> 40:48.907
I look at you
sometimes, Mom...

40:48.940 --> 40:50.908
and I am just amazed.

40:50.940 --> 40:53.841
I'm happy, Alicia.
I never do anything
I don't want to do.

40:53.880 --> 40:56.019
Are you happy?

40:56.050 --> 40:58.746
Can you say you are?
I can say that I'm living

40:58.790 --> 41:00.781
the life I want.

41:00.820 --> 41:03.789
And I can say there are
a lot bigger things.

41:03.820 --> 41:04.923
No, there aren't.

41:04.960 --> 41:08.123
The older you get,
the more you realize

41:08.160 --> 41:09.957
there's only one thing:

41:10.000 --> 41:11.729
happiness.

41:11.770 --> 41:13.965
(thunder crashing in distance)

41:14.000 --> 41:16.036
(Baroque music continues)

41:29.680 --> 41:31.989
She's never gonna
divorce you, you know.

41:32.020 --> 41:34.659
Hi, Veronica. It's
nice to see you, too.

41:34.690 --> 41:35.987
She's a good person.

41:36.020 --> 41:37.180
You're exploiting her.

41:37.220 --> 41:39.859
How? By not divorcing her?

41:39.890 --> 41:41.653
Yes.

41:41.700 --> 41:43.850
You're leading her on.

41:45.130 --> 41:46.825
Let her go.

41:46.870 --> 41:49.134
What if I don't want
to let her go?

41:49.170 --> 41:50.990
Well, then you're
just being selfish.

41:51.040 --> 41:53.702
(clears throat)

41:53.740 --> 41:55.708
PETER:
Do you need
any help?

41:55.740 --> 41:57.207
Please.

41:57.240 --> 42:00.300
Excuse me... Veronica.

42:00.350 --> 42:02.671
(Baroque music continues)

42:04.990 --> 42:06.946
What do you need?

42:06.990 --> 42:09.208
Don't tell me it's
the bathroom Window again.

42:10.260 --> 42:12.785
(siren wailing in distance)

42:16.230 --> 42:18.562
What are you doing?
Getting undressed.

42:18.600 --> 42:20.022
(thunder rumbling)

42:20.070 --> 42:23.528
Are you serious?
I've never been more
serious in my life.

42:27.770 --> 42:29.704
(gasps)

42:29.740 --> 42:31.708
*
(fire truck horn blowing)

42:31.750 --> 42:33.706
(siren continues wailing)

42:33.750 --> 42:35.115
Door's unlocked.
I don't give a...

42:35.150 --> 42:37.118
(fire truck horn blowing)

42:37.150 --> 42:39.584
(Baroque music continues,
siren fading)

42:39.620 --> 42:40.746
(thunder rumbling)

42:40.790 --> 42:42.087
(panﬁng)

42:42.120 --> 42:44.156
This is about
your mother?

42:44.190 --> 42:46.021
Yes.

